<dl id="n12140l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12140l">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12140l"> 140(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ familiar ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> The mystery society of the Ojibwa has been closely studied &hellip; In the third degree <font color="green">[of initiation]</font> use is made of ginseng, &ldquo;man root,&rdquo; which is supposed to be of &ldquo;divine&rdquo; origin. &hellip; Those who have passed into the third stage become powerful magicians, who derive their power from the sky, and often have sky spirits for &ldquo;<mark>familiars</mark>.&rdquo; <small> William James Perry, <a name="ORMR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ORMR"><cite title="source">Origin of Magic and Religion</cite></a> (1923) 151-3</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12144g" href="c12all.htm#c12144g">VI.C.12:144(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
